President Putin called President Obama to discuss the U.S. proposal for a diplomatic resolution to the crisis in Ukraine. President Obama suggested that Russia put a concrete response in writing and the two presidents agreed that Secretary Kerry and Foreign Minister Lavrov would meet to discuss next steps. President Obama urged Russia to support the Ukrainian government's restrained approach and to avoid further provocations. He reiterated that the United States strongly opposes Russia's actions in violating Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity.